HOUSE BILL 1065
M3, P2 6lr2008
By: Delegates Lehman, Kaufman, J. Long, Odom, Ruth, Taveras, and Terrasa
Introduced and read first time: February 9, 2026
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Coal Combustion By–Product Materials – Grant Program and Procurement
3 Preference
4 FOR the purpose of establishing the Coal Combustion By–Product Materials Grant
5 Program in the Department of the Environment to award grants to eligible
6 manufacturers of cement, concrete, or construction materials in the State that use
7 certain coal combustion by–products; requiring each unit of State government to give
8 preference to certain bids that demonstrate the use of certain coal combustion
9 by–products when awarding procurement contracts; and generally relating to coal
10 combustion by–products.
11 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
12 Article – Environment
13 Section 2–1205(a) and (g)
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2013 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
17 Article – Environment
18 Section 9–289(a)
19 Annotated Code of Maryland
20 (2014 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
21 BY adding to
22 Article – Environment
23 Section 9–292
24 Annotated Code of Maryland
25 (2014 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
26 BY adding to
27 Article – State Finance and Procurement
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
